as.description: The element or component the Combobox.Options should render as.
as.description_zh: The element or component the Combobox.Options should render as.

static.description:
Whether the element should ignore the internally managed open/closed
state.Note: static and unmount can not be used at the same time. You will
get a TypeScript error if you try to do it.
static.description_zh:
Whether the element should ignore the internally managed open/closed
state.Note: static and unmount can not be used at the same time. You will
get a TypeScript error if you try to do it.

unmount.description:
Whether the element should be unmounted or hidden based on the
open/closed state.Note: static and unmount can not be used at the same time. You will
get a TypeScript error if you try to do it.
unmount.description_zh:
Whether the element should be unmounted or hidden based on the
open/closed state.Note: static and unmount can not be used at the same time. You will
get a TypeScript error if you try to do it.

hold.description:
Whether or not the active option should stay active even when the mouse
leaves the active option.
hold.description_zh:
Whether or not the active option should stay active even when the mouse
leaves the active option.

:open.description: Whether or not the Combobox is open.
:open.description_zh: Whether or not the Combobox is open.
